# BKQuant / Website Development — Cursor rules

## Design & UI
- Prefer a **modern, minimal** aesthetic with **generous whitespace** (use a consistent **8px or 16px** spacing rhythm in UI work).
- Typography: favor **Inter** or **system UI stacks** that approximate **SF Pro** on Apple (`ui-sans-serif, system-ui, "Inter", "Segoe UI", sans-serif`). When adding or changing fonts, prefer Inter via Google Fonts or `font-sans` with Tailwind if already in use.
- Color: use **restrained, professional** palettes (neutral grays + one primary accent); avoid loud gradients unless the user asks; high contrast for text (WCAG-friendly).
- Visual hierarchy: clear **heading levels**, readable line length for body copy, balanced alignment; subtle shadows and borders over heavy decoration.
- Motion: **subtle** only (short durations, ease-out); no gratuitous animation.

## Tech context (this repo)
- BKQuant uses **vanilla HTML + JS** (`app.js`) and **Tailwind CDN** in places; **Shadcn/ui** requires React—do not assume it unless the project is migrated.
- Prefer matching existing patterns in `styles.css` and Tailwind classes already present in `index.html`.

## Workflow
- For **large, cross-file** UI or refactors, the user prefers **Cursor Composer (multi-file mode)**.
- For design-heavy homepage or layout work, prefer **stronger models** when available (e.g. Claude Opus/Sonnet or GPT-4.1-class) — user switches this in Cursor settings.

## Code quality
- Make **focused** changes; avoid drive-by refactors unrelated to the task.
- Do not add documentation files unless the user asks.
